        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 9:24PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 924 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Freeland to near St. Charles to Henderson
to near Laingsburg. Movement was northeast at 75 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Swartz Creek, Carrollton, Rankin, Ellington, Crump, Mayville, Deford,
Crossroads Village, Shields, Byron, Nelson, Mount Morris, East
Dayton, Caro, Argentine, Fairgrove, Lake Fenton, Shiawassee National
Wildlife Refuge, Marion Springs, and Thetford Township.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
